{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"kind":"symbol","relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol"],"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To"}],"sections":[],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(_:)-1udyo","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(_:)-2xtcf","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(_:)-7fh5d","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(_:)-8whsh","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(_:)-98jdd","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(opaquePointer:)"]},{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/ptr"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/PointerWrapper-Implementations","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/StaticMutexProtocol-Implementations"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Default-Implementations","title":"Default Implementations"}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"struct","roleHeading":"Structure","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"StaticMutexRef","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib14StaticMutexRefV","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"StaticMutexRef","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"StaticMutexRef"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" works like a "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/staticmutexref"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"StaticMutexRef","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Prior to GLib 2.32, GStaticMutex had the significant advantage"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that it doesn’t need to be created at run-time, but can be defined"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at compile-time. Since 2.32, "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" can be statically allocated"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"as well, and GStaticMutex has been deprecated."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a version of our "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"give_me_next_number()"},{"text":" example using","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"a GStaticMutex:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["  int","  give_me_next_number (void)","  {","    static int current_number = 0;","    int ret_val;","    static GStaticMutex mutex = G_STATIC_MUTEX_INIT;","","    g_static_mutex_lock (&mutex);","    ret_val = current_number = calc_next_number (current_number);","    g_static_mutex_unlock (&mutex);","","    return ret_val;","  }"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Sometimes you would like to dynamically create a mutex. If you don’t"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"want to require prior calling to "},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", because your code"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"should also be usable in non-threaded programs, you are not able to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use "},{"code":"g_mutex_new()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and thus "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"text":", as that requires a prior call to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"text":". In these cases you can also use a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It must be initialized with ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_static_mutex_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" before using it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and freed with with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_free()"},{"type":"text","text":" when not needed anymore to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"free up any allocated resources."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even though "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"type":"text","text":" is not opaque, it should only be used with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the following functions, as it is defined differently on different","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"platforms.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions apart from","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_static_mutex_get_mutex()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" can also be used even if ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"has not yet been called. Then they do nothing, apart from","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_static_mutex_trylock()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" which does nothing but returning "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions are actually macros. Apart from","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"taking their addresses, you can however use them as if they were","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"functions."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"code":"GStaticMutex","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"code":"GStaticMutex","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"text":" (instead of ","typ